# B. Technical Metrics (System + Model Level)
Cost & Inference Efficiency (These map to “model execution + context + routing”) --> Average cost is misleading; tail cost matters more
    – Cost per request (avg, p90, p95)
    – Cost per successful outcome
    – Token per request (input/output split)
    – Context size growth rate (%)
    – Model routing distribution (%)
        % requests on cheap vs expensive models
    – Cost per workflow (not per call)

Variance & Tail Risk (CRITICAL) --> AI systems fail on variance, not averages
    – Cost variance (std dev / CV)
    – p95 / p99 cost ratio vs median
    – Worst-case cost per user/session
    – Retry amplification factor
        (total calls ÷ initial requests)
    – Heavy user cost concentration (%)
        e.g. top 5% users = X% of cost

Orchestration & Workflow Complexity --> (One request → multiple hidden costs (planner, validator, etc.))
    – Calls per user action
    – Retry rate (%)
    – Fallback rate to larger models (%)
    – Workflow depth (steps per request)
    – Latency per step + total latency

Retrieval & Context Efficiency (Poor retrieval multiplies downstream cost)
    – Retrieval hit rate (useful vs unused context)
    – Average retrieved tokens vs used tokens
    – Context bloat ratio
    – Cost per retrieval operation
    – Latency added by retrieval

Concurrency & Infrastructure (AI cost is driven by peaks, not averages)
    – Peak concurrent requests
    – Concurrency utilization (%)
    – Cost per peak vs average load
    – Queue time / wait time
    – Overprovisioning cost (%)

Quality, Reliability & Stability (Stability requires extra compute (retries, validation) → must be measured)
    – Success rate / task completion rate
    – Error rate / hallucination rate
    – Retry-induced success rate
    – Consistency score (same input → same output)
    – Guardrail trigger rate

Monitoring & Evaluation Overhead (These are structural costs, not optional)
    – Cost of evaluation per request
    – Logging/storage cost per interaction
    – Human-in-the-loop rate (%)
    – Model drift detection frequency


